&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/wishardofoz/"&gt;Wishard of Oz&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/wishardofoz/4594009274/" title="Oil Booms Hit Florida Gulf Coast!"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1051/4594009274_08ee7a1836_m.jpg" width="240" height="171" alt="Oil Booms Hit Florida Gulf Coast!" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although miles and miles of oil booms have been deployed along the Gulf coast this was the first I had seen of any.  On our way to School for Deacons today we saw several big trailers full of it going both east and west.  Not sure why it’s on trailers going up and down the highway with big “BP Contractor” signs on the trucks but I guess it makes them look busy.  BP is being portrayed locally as confused and clueless; and every day that another mile of the beaches and more wildlife gets fouled the more I have to agree.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Oil booms like this are really not very effective but it appears to be the best technology we have at this time.  Does it seem like we have learned very little from previous spills?&lt;/p&gt;

