&lt;p&gt;UK-DMC2 Image (C) DMCii, 2010.  All rights reserved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/oceana_flickr/"&gt;oceana.org&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/oceana_flickr/4623930993/" title="Marshlands Northwest of the Chandaleur Islands"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4037/4623930993_e338f79d9a_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Marshlands Northwest of the Chandaleur Islands" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Despite deploying mile after mile of oil containment boom to protect the coast from oiling, nearly all the boom materials we saw during our overflight had been abandoned and their integrity subsequently compromised, often resulting in scrambled masses of boom uselessly washed up against shorelines.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo by J. Short, Oceana and S. Senner, Ocean Conservancy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/oceana_flickr/"&gt;oceana.org&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/oceana_flickr/4623948625/" title="Aerial Photo of Mousse Oil in the Gulf"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3402/4623948625_532ab9acdc_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Aerial Photo of Mousse Oil in the Gulf" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oil from the Deepwater Horizon accident about 25 miles northwest of the spill source.  The oil is a classic example of mousse formation, often characterized incorrectly as dispersed oil by observers in the region.  Mousse oil actually forms naturally as oil absorbs seawater following release, and is not necessarily a result of successful dispersant application.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Offshore drilling will NEVER be safe again. &lt;a href="http://na.oceana.org/en/stopthedrill?utm_source=flickr+group&amp;amp;utm_medium=flickr&amp;amp;utm_campaign=offshore+drilling" rel="nofollow"&gt;Sign the petition&lt;/a&gt; to end offshore drilling now.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo by J. Short, Oceana and S. Senner, Ocean Conservancy&lt;/p&gt;

