&lt;p&gt;Mousse oil and associated surface sheen about 200 meters off the beach just east of South Pass channel of the Mississippi River at 5 pm Wednesday, 18 May.  The adjacent barrier beach had heavy accumulations of mousse and thicker oil on its landward side.  Several hundered meters of abandoned boom material was washed up in a tangled mass on the beach and was completely ineffective.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Offshore drilling will NEVER be safe again. &lt;a href="http://na.oceana.org/en/stopthedrill?utm_source=flickr+group&amp;amp;utm_medium=flickr&amp;amp;utm_campaign=offshore+drilling" rel="nofollow"&gt;Sign the petition&lt;/a&gt; to end offshore drilling now.&lt;br /&gt;
