&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/lalassie/"&gt;LA Lassie&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/lalassie/4672101881/" title="BP OIL SPILL IN THE GULF OF MEXICO"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4052/4672101881_babb6c252c_m.jpg" width="240" height="160" alt="BP OIL SPILL IN THE GULF OF MEXICO" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;I regret to say that this will be my last visit for awhile to our beautiful snow white beaches and our gorgeous emerald green waters of the Gulf of Mexico.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Due to the BP Oil Spill out in the Gulf, our beaches are now covered with thick&lt;br /&gt;
gooey oil intermingled with seaweed all along our coast.  It's a sad day here on&lt;br /&gt;
the gulf coast as we watch the spread of this oil ruining our beautiful beaches.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Member of the &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/groups/1390236@N25/"&gt; &lt;b&gt;Flickr Bird Brigade&lt;/b&gt; &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;i&gt;Activists for birds and wildlife&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/perdidomike/"&gt;Perdidomike&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/perdidomike/4674552453/" title="Johnsons Beach June 6, 2010"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4014/4674552453_b0e6b3e029_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Johnsons Beach June 6, 2010" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have not words to describe my feelings seeing the beautiful beaches and my favorite one this way...and its just the beginning!&lt;br /&gt;
the tar comes in all shapes and sizes, its sticky, dirty and smelly. it doesn't come off easily. &lt;br /&gt;
I saw birds and people on the beach, soon they won't be able to enjoy or live here.&lt;br /&gt;
BP is incapable of cleaning up this. The US Government is not capable of cleaning this up! But maybe there are enough people in the world who care and have the expertise to clean it.&lt;br /&gt;
Help!&lt;/p&gt;

